---

## 🧠 How It Works

1. Ultrasonic sensor measures distance continuously  
2. If no obstacle → Car moves forward  
3. If obstacle detected → Car stops  
4. Car changes direction (left/right)  
5. Moves forward again  

---

## 🧰 Components Used (Simulation)

| Component | Description |
|----------|------------|
| Arduino UNO | Main controller |
| Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04) | Distance measurement |
| L293D Motor Driver | Motor control |
| DC Motors | Movement control |
| Battery (9V) | Power supply |

---

## 🔌 Circuit Design

![Circuit Diagram](circuit-diagram.png)

> Designed and simulated using Tinkercad.

---

## 💻 Arduino Logic

```
If (distance < threshold)
{
   Stop Car
   Turn Left or Right
}
Else
{
   Move Forward
}
```

